This is not about food; it's about honesty and integrity. I stopped in to get a quick snack and beverage to go and after I paid at the front counter I must have dropped my money clip near the counter. The clip contained almost $1000 in cash, credit cards , my license and my medical ID. I returned to my son's apartment in the neighborhood and about an hour and a half later realized my money clip was not in my pocket. That empty, awful feeling set in as I retraced my steps and made a mental list of the calls I would have to make to cancel cards, etc.; not to mention kissing $1000 in cash goodbye. I knew the last place I had my clip out was Cafe Water and walked back there and approached the front counter. I explained that I may have dropped my clip in front of the store and asked if anyone had found it. The ladies at the counter asked my name and called for the manager. Within a few moments my heart rate returned to normal after they compared my license photo to the real thing and returned my money clip....fully intact! Thank you...Thank you..Thank you. It is very reassuring and rewarding to find those very honest and special people when the situation could have been nightmarish. You have made a friend and a customer forever. Thanks again and God Bless You. MT
